Azure Storage provides redundancy options to ensure data durability and availability.

Types include:

* LRS (Locally Redundant Storage)
* ZRS (Zone Redundant Storage)
* GRS (Geo-Redundant Storage)
* RA-GRS (Read Access Geo-Redundant)

For example, GRS replicates data to another region for disaster recovery.

A real-life use case is protecting critical business data.

Another example is ensuring availability during regional outages.

Redundancy options improve reliability and resilience.
